The paper presents a computational method for predicting drug-target interactions using machine learning techniques. The method involves the use of evolutionary and structural features, which are commonly used in machine learning and bioinformatics. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the paper deals with bioinformatics and drug discovery, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CE (Computational Biology and Bioinformatics) and cs.BIO (Biomolecules).
